00:12:22.190 --> 00:12:25.190
You have often probably read
the interest rate targets.

00:12:25.190 --> 00:12:27.170
The Federal Reserve
has a target.

00:12:27.170 --> 00:12:29.330
But what they're doing in
an open market operation

00:12:29.330 --> 00:12:32.950
is really buying and
selling supply of money.

00:12:32.950 --> 00:12:35.000
And when you influence
the supply of something,

00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:36.270
you change the price.

00:12:36.270 --> 00:12:39.050
And the price of money is
measured in interest rates

00:12:39.050 --> 00:12:41.700
or foreign exchange rates.

