like the Central Bank of China,

00:53:56.060 --> 00:53:59.120
some are trying to do payment
system experimentation.

00:53:59.120 --> 00:54:02.000
We talked about
Singapore and Canada.

00:54:02.000 --> 00:54:04.430
Those are real
blockchain initiatives,

00:54:04.430 --> 00:54:06.350
the payment systems.

00:54:06.350 --> 00:54:09.950
School's still out as to whether
they need to use the blockchain

00:54:09.950 --> 00:54:11.730
technology.

00:54:11.730 --> 00:54:14.250
But they are seriously
leaning in, particularly

00:54:14.250 --> 00:54:16.380
in Singapore and
Canada, saying there

00:54:16.380 --> 00:54:18.270
might be a more
resilient payment

00:54:18.270 --> 00:54:21.870
system if we use a decentralized
distributed blockchain

00:54:21.870 --> 00:54:29.000
technology based on Quorum or
Quarta or Hyperledger Fabric.

00:54:29.000 --> 00:54:32.310
I think we're a few years away
from them sort of coming--

00:54:32.310 --> 00:54:33.670
is there enough there?

00:54:33.670 --> 00:54:35.900
Enough there there
that it would be better

00:54:35.900 --> 00:54:37.220
than traditional databases?

00:54:37.220 --> 00:54:39.890
But they are definitely
putting a lot of energy--

00:54:39.890 --> 00:54:43.880
and even the European Central
Bank, with the Bank of Japan,

00:54:43.880 --> 00:54:47.000
has an initiative as well.

00:54:47.000 --> 00:54:49.700
But in the fourth category,
central bank digital currency

00:54:49.700 --> 00:54:51.350
initiatives, I
caution everybody.

00:54:51.350 --> 00:54:54.120
You don't necessarily need
to use blockchain technology.

00:54:54.120 --> 00:54:56.120
This is the part of
the course to say,

00:54:56.120 --> 00:54:58.280
this is something
clearly inspired

00:54:58.280 --> 00:55:03.380
by Satoshi Nakamoto's innovation
and inspired by stable value

00:55:03.380 --> 00:55:05.730
tokens.

00:55:05.730 --> 00:55:08.700
But when we talk about the
bank of Sweden's initiative

00:55:08.700 --> 00:55:10.200
and some of these
other initiatives,

00:55:10.200 --> 00:55:12.060
you'll find that,
to my knowledge,

00:55:12.060 --> 00:55:15.478
they're not built on
blockchain technology.

00:55:15.478 --> 00:55:17.520
That doesn't mean they
couldn't be in the future,

00:55:17.520 --> 00:55:19.530
but I think they're
important, because they're

00:55:19.530 --> 00:55:22.260
really important to
blockchain and money

00:55:22.260 --> 00:55:26.070
and how central banks are
thinking about this area

00:55:26.070 --> 00:55:28.780
right now,

00:55:28.780 --> 00:55:32.750
We talked about this last week,
the first wave of payments

00:55:32.750 --> 00:55:34.050
were all on Ethereum.

00:55:34.050 --> 00:55:37.090
And as I said, they've
moved on from Ethereum.

00:55:37.090 --> 00:55:40.540
And the second wave of the
payment system initiatives

00:55:40.540 --> 00:55:43.060
are all permission blockchains.

00:55:43.060 --> 00:55:45.850
And now they're looking
at a third wave.

00:55:45.850 --> 00:55:48.670
If there's further questions
about how central banks are

00:55:48.670 --> 00:55:51.100
looking, I'll take
them now, or we'll

