some differential interest rate

01:00:34.930 --> 01:00:37.410
and the pricing of money?

01:00:37.410 --> 01:00:40.700
And I think some would
contend you could.

01:00:40.700 --> 01:00:41.920
But on the other side--

01:00:41.920 --> 01:00:43.420
anybody want to
take the other side?

01:00:46.150 --> 01:00:49.510
The question really is
is, does the central bank

01:00:49.510 --> 01:00:50.695
want to start making loans?

01:00:53.320 --> 01:00:55.780
Now the US central bank
has a $4.5 trillion

01:00:55.780 --> 01:00:58.150
balance sheet, as we
talked about two days ago,

01:00:58.150 --> 01:01:00.380
and owns about $2--

01:01:00.380 --> 01:01:04.780
a little less than $2 trillion,
$1.5 trillion of mortgages.

01:01:04.780 --> 01:01:06.820
So in a sense, the
central bank is already

01:01:06.820 --> 01:01:09.070
making a credit decision.

01:01:09.070 --> 01:01:11.840
They're lending to
the mortgage market.

01:01:11.840 --> 01:01:14.340
But the question is, do you
want to go even further and have

01:01:14.340 --> 01:01:18.060
the central bank picking
individual companies

01:01:18.060 --> 01:01:21.180
or individual
homeowners to lend to?

01:01:21.180 --> 01:01:26.040
And that's what-- if it
got to any scale or size,

01:01:26.040 --> 01:01:27.050
they talk about.

