important role in the economy.

01:18:16.140 --> 01:18:18.650
We already live in
an electronic age.

01:18:18.650 --> 01:18:23.510
But they really are absolutely
at the epicenter of money

01:18:23.510 --> 01:18:26.930
and how money's been defined
for 300 or 400 years.

01:18:26.930 --> 01:18:31.070
Payment systems and Fiat
currencies have had challenges.

01:18:31.070 --> 01:18:32.960
I still continue to
think blockchain--

01:18:32.960 --> 01:18:34.580
I told you, I'm
not a maximalist,

01:18:34.580 --> 01:18:37.820
but blockchain technology
can be a catalyst for change.

01:18:37.820 --> 01:18:42.740
Central bank digital
currencies is evidence of that,

01:18:42.740 --> 01:18:45.270
even if it's not based
on blockchain technology.

01:18:45.270 --> 01:18:50.210
I think it's partly inspired
and urged on by this.

01:18:50.210 --> 01:18:53.210
It doesn't solve what
blockchain technology

01:18:53.210 --> 01:18:55.370
would do for it, but--

01:18:55.370 --> 01:18:58.860
I think that central banks
by and large are monitoring.

01:18:58.860 --> 01:19:01.640
They're exploring
payment systems,

01:19:01.640 --> 01:19:05.240
and a handful are looking
at the central bank

01:19:05.240 --> 01:19:06.650
digital currencies.

01:19:06.650 --> 01:19:08.360
I think-- and this is
